NFS volume management :

Basic NFS Commands (NetApp style)
Enable NFS
vserver nfs create -vserver vs1
Create volume
volume create -vserver vs1 -volume data_vol -aggregate aggr1 -size 100GB
Create export policy
export-policy create -vserver vs1 -policyname default
Add rule (who can access)
export-policy rule create -vserver vs1 -policyname default -clientmatch 0.0.0.0/0 -rorule any
Assign policy to volume
volume modify -vserver vs1 -volume data_vol -policy default
Client mount (Linux)
mount -t nfs server_ip:/data_vol /mnt

🔁 ASYNCHRONOUS (Most Common)        ⚡ SYNCHRONOUS (Real-Time)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

# Create relationship
snapmirror create                    snapmirror create
-source-path src:vol                -source-path src:vol
-destination-path dest:vol          -destination-path dest:vol
-type XDP                           -type SYNC


# Initialize (first copy)
snapmirror initialize               snapmirror initialize
-destination-path dest:vol          -destination-path dest:vol


# Schedule updates (IMPORTANT)
snapmirror modify                   ❌ Not needed
-destination-path dest:vol
-schedule hourly


# Update manually
snapmirror update                   ❌ Not used (auto sync)
-destination-path dest:vol


# Check status
snapmirror show                     snapmirror show


# Break (failover)
snapmirror break                    snapmirror break
